'''Off Color Brewing''' is an American [[craft beer]] brewery in the [[Logan Square, Chicago|Logan Square]] neighborhood of [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]].<ref>
*Thiel, Julia (June 19, 2013). [http://www.chicagoreader.com/Bleader/archives/2013/06/19/a-look-at-the-new-off-color-brewery "A Look at the New Off Color Brewery"], ''Chicago Reader''. Retrieved April 23, 2014.
*Cooley, Sean (June 26, 2013). [http://www.thrillist.com/drink/chicago/chis-most-anticipated-brewery-taps-its-first-beers-heres-where-to-get-them "Chi's Most Anticipated Brewery Taps Its First Beers; Here's Where to Get Them"], Thrillist. Retrieved April 23, 2014.
*Miller, Norman (January 16, 2014). [http://www.seacoastonline.com/articles/20140116-LIFE-401160320 "Off Color Brewing Taps into Early Beer Styles"], SeacoastOnline. Retrieved April 23, 2014.
*[http://www.beeradvocate.com/beer/profile/31678/ Off Color Brewing], BeerAdvocate. Retrieved April 23, 2014.</ref><ref name=RateBeer>[http://www.ratebeer.com/brewers/off-color-brewing/16683/ Off Color Brewing], RateBeer. Retrieved April 23, 2014.</ref> The brewery began in early 2013 as a partnership between John Laffler, formerly with [[Goose Island Brewery]], and Dave Bleitner, formerly with [[Two Brothers Brewing]].<ref>Noel, Josh (November 28, 2012). [http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-11-28/business/ct-biz-1128-off-color-brewing-20121128_1_craft-beer-breweries-bourbon-county-stout "Off Color Brewing Hopes to Tap Underserved Chicago Craft Beer Market"], ''Chicago Tribune''. Retrieved April 23, 2014.</ref> The modus operandi of Off Color's founders when they began operation was to focus on brewing forgotten styles of beer, particularly those made in Germany before ''[[Reinheitsgebot]]'' (i.e. the Bavarian Purity Law) was proclaimed in the late 15th century, effectively condemning myriad styles of beer not made solely with barley, water, and hops.<ref>Dudek, Mitch (November 27, 2012). [http://www.suntimes.com/16665444-761/logan-square-brewers-hoping-to-serve-up-beers-not-tasted-in-500-years.html "Logan Square Brewers Hoping to Serve Up Beers Not Tasted in 500 Years"], ''Chicago Sun-Times''. Retrieved April 23, 2014.</ref>

